text: Jeffrey Allen Thompsonhttp://grfx.cstv.com/photos/schools/aub/sports/w-gym/auto_pdf/0809-media- guide-6.pdf (born November 22, 1961) is an American artistic gymnastics coach. Coaching for thirty years, he has worked extensively on the NCAA collegiate scene but has also worked within club gymnastics. After holding assistant coach positions at Wisconsin-Madison, Illinois and Louisiana State for ten years, Thompson was appointed the head coach of the Auburn Tigers women's gymnastics program for the incoming 2000 season. He spent eleven seasons at Auburn, leading the Tigers to seven consecutive NCAA Regional appearances.http://www.auburntigers.com/sports/w-gym/mtt/thompson_jeff00.html ==References== Category:1961 births Category:Living people Category:People from Fort Thomas, Kentucky Category:University of Kentucky alumni
